  <section id="were-helping-by" class="slider-slice_container paragraph-container">
    <section class="text_link_carousel black title-centre" aria-labelledby="carousel-heading">
            <div class="article_wrapper text-link-heading-container">
                <h3>
            We're helping by...
        </h3>
                      </div>
            <div class="splide">
        <div class="splide__track article_wrapper">
          <ul class="splide__list">
                                                                    <li class="splide__slide">
                <figure>
                  <img src="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_320/public/2021-10/tiger.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=iRIt0H06"
                       srcset="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_320/public/2021-10/tiger.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=iRIt0H06 320w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_640/public/2021-10/tiger.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=wDZnp-X5 640w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_768/public/2021-10/tiger.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=GevUDqEo 768w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1024/public/2021-10/tiger.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=LRIXWHxT 1024w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1200/public/2021-10/tiger.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=jO8avdnz 1200w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1440/public/2021-10/tiger.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=eQ4Q3IbV 1440w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1536/public/2021-10/tiger.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=C1Lsnsej 1536w"
                       alt="Bengal tiger (Panthera tigris tigris), female resting and looking up Kanha National Park, India. "
                       sizes="(max-width:768px) 95vw, 25vw"
                  />
                                      <div class="splide-copyright">© naturepl.com / Axel Gomille / WWF</div>
                                    <figcaption>
                    <h4>Restoring the lungs of our earth for tigers and people</h4>
                    <div class="figure-text-container">
                      <p><p>Climate change is causing more extreme weather, storms, floods and wildfires and putting tigers precious forest habitats under threat.</p>

<p><strong lang="EN-GB">At WWF we’re working with governments and local people to help protect and restore these forests areas</strong>, forests that not only provide home to tigers but also provide livelihoods to people and are vital in<strong lang="EN-GB"> absorbing harmful carbon from the atmosphere</strong>.</p>

<p>Precious tiger habitats also overlap nine of Asia’s watersheds, supplying water to over 800 million people. Healthy forests in these river areas play an important role in reducing the risk of devastating floods and droughts, as well as storing huge amounts of harmful carbon.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
</p>
                    </div>
                  </figcaption>
                                  </figure>
              </li>
                                                                    <li class="splide__slide">
                <figure>
                  <img src="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_320/public/2021-10/snow_leopard.jpg?h=6f8d68bc&amp;itok=93bUSV_L"
                       srcset="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_320/public/2021-10/snow_leopard.jpg?h=6f8d68bc&amp;itok=93bUSV_L 320w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_640/public/2021-10/snow_leopard.jpg?h=6f8d68bc&amp;itok=x1AgJUh6 640w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_768/public/2021-10/snow_leopard.jpg?h=6f8d68bc&amp;itok=Dio4r_7b 768w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1024/public/2021-10/snow_leopard.jpg?h=6f8d68bc&amp;itok=WHt2nI_J 1024w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1200/public/2021-10/snow_leopard.jpg?h=6f8d68bc&amp;itok=cCmP4g39 1200w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1440/public/2021-10/snow_leopard.jpg?h=6f8d68bc&amp;itok=vFg7QPVh 1440w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1536/public/2021-10/snow_leopard.jpg?h=6f8d68bc&amp;itok=0wIZyZvf 1536w"
                       alt="Close up portrait of a snow leopard (Panthera uncia) cub"
                       sizes="(max-width:768px) 95vw, 25vw"
                  />
                                      <div class="splide-copyright">© Shutterstock / Blanka Berankova / WWF</div>
                                    <figcaption>
                    <h4>Reducing climate pressures on people and snow leopards</h4>
                    <div class="figure-text-container">
                      <p><p>As temperatures climb and climate change grows more intense, it increases the pressure on snow leopards and people.</p>

<p>For the many people who share their mountain home with the snow leopard, its habitat is an essential source of food and medicine, and wood for shelter, heat and fuel.</p>

<p><strong lang="EN-GB">We’re working with communities on farming that’s more resistant to climate change</strong>, and building livelihoods that are sustainable – so they will provide for the next generation.&nbsp;</p>
</p>
                    </div>
                  </figcaption>
                                  </figure>
              </li>
                                                                    <li class="splide__slide">
                <figure>
                  <img src="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_320/public/2020-03/Sky%20seagrass.jpg?h=c3635fa2&amp;itok=vo9MJRcq"
                       srcset="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_320/public/2020-03/Sky%20seagrass.jpg?h=c3635fa2&amp;itok=vo9MJRcq 320w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_640/public/2020-03/Sky%20seagrass.jpg?h=c3635fa2&amp;itok=WMAI9PF- 640w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_768/public/2020-03/Sky%20seagrass.jpg?h=c3635fa2&amp;itok=bDRbNKXM 768w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1024/public/2020-03/Sky%20seagrass.jpg?h=c3635fa2&amp;itok=FX3ozt2v 1024w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1200/public/2020-03/Sky%20seagrass.jpg?h=c3635fa2&amp;itok=mUS47lnT 1200w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1440/public/2020-03/Sky%20seagrass.jpg?h=c3635fa2&amp;itok=KJBf_yq8 1440w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1536/public/2020-03/Sky%20seagrass.jpg?h=c3635fa2&amp;itok=GPioamXH 1536w"
                       alt=""
                       sizes="(max-width:768px) 95vw, 25vw"
                  />
                                      <div class="splide-copyright">© Lewis Jefferies / WWF-UK</div>
                                    <figcaption>
                    <h4>Planting seagrass to help fight climate change</h4>
                    <div class="figure-text-container">
                      <p><p>Seagrass provides a home for a vast array of sea life, but did you know it can also help in the fight against climate change?</p>

<p>Even though seagrass only covers 0.2% of the seafloor, it absorbs 10% of the ocean’s carbon each year, making it an incredible tool in the fight against climate change.</p>

<p>Together, with Sky Zero and Swansea University, <strong lang="EN-GB">we’ve planted 750,000 seagrass seeds which will grow into an ocean meadow - fighting climate change and providing a home for marine life.</strong>&nbsp;</p>
</p>
                    </div>
                  </figcaption>
                                  </figure>
              </li>
                                                                    <li class="splide__slide">
                <figure>
                  <img src="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_320/public/2021-11/_WW2141691.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=s35AP6HT"
                       srcset="https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_320/public/2021-11/_WW2141691.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=s35AP6HT 320w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_640/public/2021-11/_WW2141691.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=30MBEX9F 640w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_768/public/2021-11/_WW2141691.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=ncOiOC8u 768w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1024/public/2021-11/_WW2141691.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=rRtOutGh 1024w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1200/public/2021-11/_WW2141691.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=iocCfqEv 1200w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1440/public/2021-11/_WW2141691.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=XU4oPKR3 1440w,
                           https://www.wwf.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/text_link_carousel_slider_1536/public/2021-11/_WW2141691.jpg?h=82f92a78&amp;itok=UsH16vIh 1536w"
                       alt="Bitaté Uru Eu Wau Wau, the president of the Uru Eu Wau Wau Idigenous People&#039;s Association"
                       sizes="(max-width:768px) 95vw, 25vw"
                  />
                                      <div class="splide-copyright">© Marizilda Cruppe / WWF-UK</div>
                                    <figcaption>
                    <h4>Working with communities to protect the amazon rainforest</h4>
                    <div class="figure-text-container">
                      <p><p>The Amazon is home to millions of people and species, and it’s also <strong lang="EN-GB">one of our biggest allies in fighting climate change</strong> – but it’s being destroyed.</p>

<p>With your help, WWF are supporting communities by providing drone training.  The drones will be used as a tool to help monitor protected areas, deforestation alerts and land grabbing – <strong lang="EN-GB">helping to protect their home and the trees that are vital in fighting climate change.</strong>&nbsp;</p>
</p>
                    </div>
                  </figcaption>
                                  </figure>
              </li>
                      </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="splide__arrows splide__arrows--ltr">
          <button
            class="splide__arrow splide__arrow--prev"
